    "REASON: The proposed roof extension by reason of its inappropriate design, scale and massing would represent a  discordant  and visible feature when viewed from both the public and private realm. The development is therefore considered to have a detrimental impact on the character and appearance of the host building, its setting along Hemingford Road and its wider setting within the Barnsbury Conservation Area. The proposal is contrary to policy 9 of islington's Core Strategy 2011, policies  D4(Designing in context), D11(Alterations and extensions), D25 ( Roof extensions)  of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002, Islington Urban Design Guide 2006,conservation guidance note 10  and PPS 5."
